{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>This entry represents a group of DnaJ homologue subfamily C proteins, including GRV2 from Arabidopsis and DNAJC13 (also known as RME-8) from humans. They are involved in endocytosis. GRV2 functions in vesicle trafficking from the multivesicular body/pre-vacuolar compartment to the lytic vacuole [[cite:PUB00097656]]. In Arabidopsis grv2 mutants display enlarged aggregated endosomes, defective vacuole biogenesis and embryogenesis, and reduced gravitropic responses [[cite:PUB00097661], [cite:PUB00097659], [cite:PUB00097660]]. DNAJC13 plays a role in the endosomal transport machinery, in which it coordinates the activity of the WASH complex with the function of the retromer SNX dimer to control endosomal tubulation [[cite:PUB00091010]].</p>\n\n<p>DNAJC13 has been linked to Parkinson disease [[cite:PUB00097657]]. In humans, DNAJC13 localizes to early endosomal compartments via an N-terminal PI(3)P targeting motif and binds the co-chaperone Heat shock cognate-70 (Hsc70) through the central J domain, whereas the remainder interacts with the BAR-domain containing sorting nexin 1 (SNX1) protein and the FAM21 subunit of the WASH complex\n[[cite:PUB00097658]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR36983" "DNAJ HOMOLOG SUBFAMILY C MEMBER 13"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "DnaJ homologue subfamily C, GRV2/DNAJC13", "short" "GRV2/DNAJC13"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 0, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 1356, "taxa" 5475, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 4518, "sets" 0, "proteins" 4518, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 1256}, "pathways" 1}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR044978", :literature {"PUB00097657" {"URL" nil, "issue" "2", "authors" ["Gustavsson EK" "Trinh J" "Guella I" "Vilarino-Guell C" "